{"lemma":"خَبَرَيْ","slug":"خَبَرَيْ","root":"خ.ب.ر","root_slug":"خ-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَبَر","root":"خبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9886","","n9889","n9890","n9891","n9892","n9893"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to try, to test","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience, to know by experience, to know well, to know thoroughly","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to know thoroughly, to be fully acquainted with"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to notify, to advise, to apprise, to inform (someone بِ (bi, “about”))"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"report, message, notification"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"proposition (“statement expressing something that is either true or false”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"news"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"information, intelligence"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rumor, story"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"matter, affair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"predicate of a nominal clause"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of خَبَرَ (ḵabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knowledge, information"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xa.ba.ra/","/xa.bu.ra/","/xab.ba.ra/","/xa.bar/","/xibr/","/xubr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9886","headword_ar":"خَبُرَ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuwrN","text_ar":"خُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axtbr","text_ar":"اختبر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txb~r","text_ar":"تخبّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knew;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed, knowledge;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aYo'K","text_ar":"بِشَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to its internal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"real, state"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarahu","text_ar":"خَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, MS,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, MS; *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirahu","text_ar":"خَبِرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] (A,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axtbirhu","text_ar":"اختبِرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txb~rhu","text_ar":"تخبّرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knew it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealimahu","text_ar":"عَلِمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb;) [generally meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to its internal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"real, state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabura bihi","text_ar":"خَبُرَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", its simple subst., as distinguished from its inf. n.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^ayona xabarota ha*aA AlA^amora","text_ar":"مِنْ اَيْنَ خَبَرْتَ هَذَا الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in a copy of the S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirota","text_ar":"خَبِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in another copy of the S, and so in the A, where it is expressly said to be with kesr,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whence knewest thou this thing?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A. *) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarahu","text_ar":"خَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborapN","text_ar":"خِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or the latter is a simple subst.; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axtbrhu","text_ar":"اختبرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is the more common in this sense]; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tried, made trial of, made experiment of, tested, proved, assayed, proved by trial"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experiment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experience him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K.) Hence the phrase, (S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^axoburan~a xabaraka","text_ar":"لَاَخْبُرَنَّ خَبَرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) in some good lexicons"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuboraka","text_ar":"خُبْرَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [and so in the CK, but this I think to be a mistake, suggested by the explanation, which is not literal,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aEolaman~a Eilomaka","text_ar":"لَاَعْلَمَنَّ عِلْمَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly know thy knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what thou knowest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but here means, as is shown by the manner in which the phrase that it explains is mentioned in the S,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly try, prove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"test, thy state, and so know what thou knowest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) [Hence, also,] the saying of Abu-dDardà,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu Aln~aAsa Auxoburo taqolihimo","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ النَّاسَ اُخْبُرْ تَقْلِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqolihi","text_ar":"تَقْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I found the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be persons of whom it is said thus: ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Try, prove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"test,"},{"kind":"text","text":"them, or him, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou wilt hate them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e. there is not one [of them] but his conduct is hated when it is tried, or proved, or tested: (K:) or when thou triest, provest, or testest, them, thou wilt hate them: the imperative form being used, but the meaning being that of an enunciative: (S, A, L, B:) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a verb of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEaAlu","text_ar":"اَفْعَالُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alquluwbi","text_ar":"القُلُوبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which govern two objective complements; therefore"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Auxoburo taqolihimo","text_ar":"اُخْبُرْ تَقْلِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Auxoburo taqolihi","text_ar":"اُخْبُرْ تَقْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoliy~iyna Einoda Alxiborapi","text_ar":"مَقْلِيِّينَ عِنْدَ الخِبْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoliy~FA End Alxbrp","text_ar":"مَقْلِيًّا عند الخبرة"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabara AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"خَبَرَ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and, as appears from a passage in the L, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xb~rhA","text_ar":"خبّرها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He furrowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ploughed, the land for sowing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabara","text_ar":"خَبَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~aEaAma","text_ar":"الطَّعَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the food greasy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put grease to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabira","text_ar":"خَبِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a place)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaboraA='","text_ar":"خَبْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounded with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lote-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"خَبِرَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, abounded with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAr","text_ar":"خَبَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft soil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 3]. (K.)       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xbrt","text_ar":"خبرت"},{"kind":"text","text":", [probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaburato","text_ar":"خَبُرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazurato","text_ar":"غَزُرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuwrN","text_ar":"خُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounded with milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["K","S","A","Msb","MS","L","B","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9889","headword_ar":"خَبْرٌ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trees of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lote-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Lth, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with abundant herbage around them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirN","text_ar":"خَبِرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, K:) [both coll. gen. ns.:] ns. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborapN","text_ar":"خَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirapN","text_ar":"خَبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seed-produce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place where water rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stagnates, in a mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place where water has fallen, such as the water-course has furrowed"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~ara","text_ar":"خَبَّرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabara","text_ar":"خَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the summits"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^uws","text_ar":"رُوُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":") ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of mountains"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and through which one wades."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A large"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaboraA='u","text_ar":"خَبْرَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborN","text_ar":"خِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) but this last is disallowed, in the sense above-explained, by AHeyth; and others say that the first word is better: (TA:) pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuwrN","text_ar":"خُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, by way of comparison thereto, (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel abounding with milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborN","text_ar":"خِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobuwrapN","text_ar":"مَخْبُورَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","K","Kr","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n9890","headword_ar":"خُبْرٌ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborN","text_ar":"خِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", an inf. n., (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", also an inf. n., (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborapN","text_ar":"خُبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborapN","text_ar":"خِبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobarapN","text_ar":"مَخْبَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilomN","text_ar":"عِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aYo'K","text_ar":"بِشَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]:"},{"kind":"page_break","n":696},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozN","text_ar":"خُبْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the secret internal state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibozapN","text_ar":"خِبْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubozapN","text_ar":"خُبْزَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge of the external and internal state;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of secret internal circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"properties;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this necessarily involves acquaintance with external things. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY bihi xuborN","text_ar":"لِى بِهِ خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborapN","text_ar":"خِبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have knowledge of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA liY bihi xuborN","text_ar":"مَا لِى بِهِ خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not knowledge of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiborapN","text_ar":"خِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyrN","text_ar":"خَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborapN","text_ar":"خُبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n9891","headword_ar":"خِبْرٌ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and see also 3:       -A3-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9892","headword_ar":"خَبَرٌ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally] an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirahu","text_ar":"خَبِرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Information; a piece of information; a notification; intelligence; an announcement; news; tidings; a piece of news; an account; a narration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative; a story;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaA^N","text_ar":"نَبَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that comes to one from a person of whom he asks it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabaA^N","text_ar":"نَبَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are not synonymous; for, accord. to Er-Rághib and others, the latter relates to a thing of great importance: and accord. to the leading authorities in lexicology and the science of conventional language, the former signifies properly, and in its common acceptation,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is related from another or others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"to which authors on the Arabic language add, that it may be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"true"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is related from another"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"others, and talked of:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobaArN","text_ar":"اَخْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axaAbiyru","text_ar":"اَخَابِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  By the relaters of traditions, it is used as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HadiyvN","text_ar":"حَدِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tradition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narrative relating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"describing, a saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an action &c. of Mohammad"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or this latter term is applied to what comes from the Prophet; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabarN","text_ar":"خَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what comes from another than the Prophet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from him or another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avarN","text_ar":"اَثَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to what comes from a Companion of the Prophet; but it may also be applied to a saying of the Prophet. (Kull p. 152.) ―         -b4-  [In grammar, as correlative of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubotadaA^N","text_ar":"مُبْتَدَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An enunciative:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and as correlative of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisomN","text_ar":"اِسْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"predicate"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the non-attributive verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like, and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAda","text_ar":"كَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] ―         -b5-  Also A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amoru Al~a*iY huwa Ealyohi","text_ar":"الاَمْرُ الَّذِى هُوَ عَليْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 20.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","MF","Msb","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n9893","headword_ar":"خَبِرٌ","root":"xbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyrN","text_ar":"خَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaborN","text_ar":"خَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirapN","text_ar":"خَبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN xabirapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ خَبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoDiEN xabirN","text_ar":"مَوْضِعٌ خَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabirN","text_ar":"خَبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuborN","text_ar":"خُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}